<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[1157,1436,690,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref11914" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D. (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific Selenocephalinae leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">Zhang &amp; Webb 1996: 25</bibRefCitation>
and designated as 
<typeStatus box="[361,467,727,753]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Among the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1870" box="[735,855,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,855,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Drabescus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without basal processes on the aedeagal shaft, this species can easily be recognised by the short aedeagal shaft with apical half expanded laterally and the style without subapical lobe. The female can be recognised by the sternite VII with a median V-shaped excavation on the posterior margin. This species occurs in southern states of peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[823,881,835,861]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[895,1079,835,861]" country="India" name="Andhra Pradesh" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Andhra Pradesh</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1090,1208,835,861]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1218,1352,835,862]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
) and in northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[261,319,871,897]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[333,464,871,898]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
).
